data.content:
The arguments to `Assert.AreEqual` are swapped. MSTest's signature is `Assert.AreEqual(expected, actual)` — expected value first, actual result second. When a test fails, the error message will incorrectly report which value was expected vs. actual.

**Fix:**

```csharp
// Before
Assert.AreEqual(result, 5);
Assert.AreEqual(result, 0);

// After
Assert.AreEqual(5, result);
Assert.AreEqual(0, result);
```
